data.name: Chicken Alfredo with Garlic Bread
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy and rich Chicken Alfredo served with buttery garlic bread, perfect for a comforting meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook fettuccine pasta according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.

In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper, then cook in the skillet for about 6-7 minutes on each side until cooked through. Remove from skillet and slice.
In the same skillet, add butter and minced garlic. Sauté for about 1 minute until fragrant.
Pour in the heavy cream and bring to a gentle simmer. Stir in the Parmesan cheese until melted and smooth.
Add the cooked pasta to the sauce, tossing to coat. Add sliced chicken on top.
For garlic bread, preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). Spread butter mixed with minced garlic on slices of bread, place on a baking sheet, and bake for 10-12 minutes until golden.
Serve Chicken Alfredo with garlic bread on the side, garnished with fresh parsley.
data.detailedName: Creamy Chicken Alfredo with Buttery Garlic Bread
data.modifiersForBase: Added garlic bread for a complete meal.
